    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-16T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-16T20:00:00-05:00" n="148"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3731/910: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-16T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 16, 1934—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>149. Your 396, August 15. Since the last exception in the proviso of new Article
                    V is clearly intended to apply to control programs such as the sugar and
                    tobacco, you may agree to the deletion of the phrase “other than dutiable sugar
                    or tobacco or dutiable products thereof”. In order that there may be a clear
                    understanding, however, please present an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>
                    explicitly stating that the exception covers the import restrictions imposed or
                    to be imposed by this Government on sugar and tobacco.</p>
                <p>The word “is” before the word “restricted” should be changed to “may be.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
